Vagabondvying 2018-05-13: I feel like Estonia and Lithuania and Latvia likely are better than the upward but already stagnating Ukraine and Belarus. It's probably also worth noting that Estonia is relative to its neighbours and not in the context of capitalism.

I came to Sweden previously going "my god so much nature!", over time I grew to realize that in many ways it was just a shrunk down Britain with a nicer facade in the cities.

There's a reason why Italy and Greece have so much nature, because they're so deeply in arrears and as such you really get a sense of the sheer scale when you're in the middle of the trees up their mountain or just sprawled out on a beach. Sweden has a lot, it's hikeable and mountable and climbable and paddleable and cycleable but it just doesn't have the sort of dramatic personality of a Greece or anything.
